Subtitle of House Bill 1555
TO ESTABLISH UNIFORM PROCEDURES FOR FILLING A VACANCY IN A MUNICIPAL
OFFICE.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 2 to House Bill 1555
Amend House Bill 1555 as engrossed S3/31/25 (version: 3/31/25 02:29:10 PM):
Page 2, line 5, delete "a quorum of the whole number of" and substitute "the
remaining members of"
AND
Page 2, delete line 10, and substitute the following:
"municipality shall not be appointed to fill a vacancy under this section in
municipalities with a population of fifty thousand (50,000) or more; or"
AND
Page 2, delete lines 15 and 16, and substitute the following "(B)(i) If the
governing body of a municipality calls"
AND
Page 2, delete line 22, and substitute the following:
"municipality may be appointed under subdivision (a)(2)(B)(i) of this section
to serve in the office until the vacancy is filled at a special election."
